{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"gawky-koi-grain","description":"## Why\n\nThe bespoke `verifier_cfg` downgrades the verify pass from the default frontier model (Opus) to a\ndecisive non-frontier model (Sonnet) unless the operator explicitly chose a model. The workflow verify\nstep does NOT apply this today (it uses the runner default), so migrating drift-refresh off bespoke\n(WS1) would lose the downgrade. Reproduce it declaratively via the existing per-step `model:` key\n(`resolve_model`, WS-D3: step > workflow > cfg). Because this makes a per-step `model:` key first-class\non a shipped gate workflow, it must also be reflected in the visual editor UX — today only the\nworkflow-level model is carried in BPMN, so editing the workflow in the visual editor could silently\ndrop a step's model.\n\n## What\n\n- Pin the workflow verify step's `model:` to the decisive non-frontier verifier (Sonnet) by default,\n  resolved via the existing per-step `model:` / `resolve_model` path; honor an explicit operator model\n  override (parity with `verifier_cfg`).\n- Visual editor: surface the per-step `model` field in the properties panel (a select over the known\n  model ladder), and make a per-step `model` round-trip through BPMN export/import so a visual edit +\n  save never drops it.\n- BPMN back-compat: importing a pre-existing BPMN document that lacks the per-step model attribute\n  defaults gracefully to \"no per-step override\" (the step falls back to the workflow/cfg model via\n  `resolve_model`), never errors.\n- Document the per-step `model:` knob in the workflow-authoring + editor docs.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn scope: the verify-step model pin + override, the editor properties-panel field, BPMN round-trip +\nback-compat, and docs. Out of scope: drift-refresh migration / bespoke deletion (WS1), token chunking\n(WS3 sizes against the model this story pins), the coach-gate nit (WS4). Touches:\n`src/rebar/llm/workflow/gates/plan-review.yaml`, `runs.py` (`resolve_model`), `bpmn.py`, `editor.py`,\nand the workflow-authoring/editor docs.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The workflow verify step pins the decisive non-frontier verifier model (Sonnet) by default,\n      resolved via the existing per-step `model:` / `resolve_model` path.\n- [ ] An explicit operator model override is honored on the verify step (parity with `verifier_cfg`).\n- [ ] The visual editor properties panel lets a user view/edit a step's `model`.\n- [ ] A per-step `model` survives a BPMN export → import (visual-edit → save) round-trip unchanged; a\n      regression test asserts the round-trip.\n- [ ] Importing a legacy BPMN document that lacks the per-step model attribute succeeds and falls back\n      to the workflow/cfg model (no error, no per-step override).\n- [ ] Authoring + editor docs document the per-step `model:` knob.\n- [ ] `make lint` + `make check` + the full test suite pass.\n","id":"bc6e-71cf-255a-47f7","parent_id":"4e70-0cd4-0d04-4d31","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"WS2: Per-step verifier model:key (Sonnet downgrade) surfaced in the visual editor UX"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782581459683192001,"uuid":"4ead5501-9f6f-4031-8f02-7bbee23ef6d2"}